Var is used to create variables 

Variable names cab contain letters, digits, _ and $. They can start with an _ and $. Case-Sensitive 

JS always stores a number in 64 bits 

NaN and Infinity are numbers in JS

console.clear() - method clears up the console every time we reload

var.toString() - converts a number to string 

var.parseInt() - convert a string to am integer 

var.parseFloat() - converts a string to a floating point number 

var.toFixed() - takes a floating number and round it off to a given position, it no index is given in the parameters, it round up to nearest integer , otherwise to rounds up to the given index.













